E'Man: Hi, Maria. Haven''t seen you at the biology lab lately.\nWoman: I know. I actually dropped that class. I''m seriously thinking about changing my major from pre-med to journalism.\nMan: Really? That''s a huge shift. What brought that on?\nWoman: Well, I spent the summer writing for the campus newspaper, and I loved every minute of it. The lab work just wasn''t making me happy.\nMan: But you''ve already taken so many science prerequisites. Won''t you lose a lot of credits?\nWoman: Not as many as you''d think. The academic advisor told me my science classes will cover all my general education electives.\nMan: That''s lucky! Are you worried about what your parents will say?\nWoman: A little. My dad really wanted me to be a doctor like him. But I have to do what I''m passionate about.\nMan: Have you talked to him yet?\nWoman: No, I''m planning to call him this weekend. Wish me luck.', TRUE),

